                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/15316.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Canada</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vera Cruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-27T17:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 27, 1915—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>By special messenger: Zapata forces defeated Carranza forces in Mexico City.
                    Capital entirely cut off from the world. Carranza rushing all available men to
                    Mexico City. If Zapata forces are driven back I fear horrors will follow. No
                    food in Mexico City.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
